<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Pia Miller and her multi-millionaire American talent agent boyfriend Patrick Whitesell have been separated for months due to the pandemic. </p>

<p>But the former Home and Away actress, 36, was positively glowing after the couple were reunited on Wednesday. </p>

<p>Taking to Instagram, Pia beamed as she sat next to Patrick, 55, in a car.</p>

<p>Together again! On Wednesday, Pia Miller, 36, was reunited with her multi-millionaire agent boyfriend Patrick Whitesell, 55, after spending months apart due to COVID-19. Both pictured</p>

<p>Patrick looked equally as happy to be back with his actress ladylove, with him leaning in close to be next to her. </p>

<p>'Can't keep us apart! Two Ps in a pod,' she wrote, adding a love heart emoji. </p>

<p>Pia kept it glam in a spaghetti strap top with her signatures brunette tresses down. </p>

<p>Meanwhile, Patrick looked positively dashing in an always fashionable black t-shirt as he flashed his million dollar smile.  </p>

<p>Memories: As evidenced by her Instagram, they were last together in February, when Pia visited her beau at his LA mansion </p>

<p>With the coronavirus pandemic prompting international border closures, Pia has been living in Sydney while Patrick has been based in Los Angeles. </p>

<p>As evidenced by her Instagram, they were last together in February, when Pia visited her beau at his LA mansion.</p>

<p>Pia has made no secret of the fact she has been missing her beau, while the pair have been forced to spend time apart.    </p>

<p>Loved-up: In March, she shared a throwback photo of the two of them together during a romantic holiday in Italy</p>

<p>In March, she shared a throwback photo of the two of them together during a romantic holiday in Italy. </p>

<p>'Repost PW: #Throw back better times. Italy, we will be back!' she captioned the moonlight photo.</p>

<p>She added: 'Yes we will! #happytimesthrowback'.</p>

<p>Pia was first linked to the Hollywood power agent in August last year, following her split with her longtime fiancé, Tyson Mullane, 31, in April.  </p>

<p>Stepping out: The couple made their red carpet debut when they attended the Oscars together in February this year in Los Angeles</p>

<p>The couple made their public debut at a Halloween party in Los Angeles in October, amid reports they'd started dating back in May.</p>

<p>She finally made their relationship Instagram official on Christmas Eve, sharing a loved-up photo with him outside of the Louvre in Paris, and captioning it 'P²'.</p>

<p>The couple made their red carpet debut when they attended the Oscars together in February this year in Los Angeles.</p>

<p>Going public: Pia made their relationship Instagram official on Christmas Eve, sharing a loved-up photo with him outside of the Louvre in Paris, and captioning it 'P²'</p>
